    "created_at": "2012-01-30T23:06:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-30T23:06:02Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, it will work if no arguments are to be passed, which is already a nice feature.\n\nWe already use `--` to stop parsing, but even that won't quite work because the first positional argument (the first one past `--`) is interpreted as file_to_run.  This action should probably be skipped if the module is specified.\n\nThe relevant line: https://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/IPython/frontend/terminal/ipapp.py#L309\n"
  },
